profile_positions.description:
Thermal & Flow Analysis Engineer, Computational Fluid Dynamic (CFD)
›	Manage, run and control Computational Fluid Dynamic (CFD) simulations of Lithography machines and wafer handling systems;
›	Investigate wind turbines thermal behaviour to produce CFD models;
›	Study the Joule-Thomson effect on air-purging systems, running Thermal & Flow CFD simulations for design improvements;
›	Establish meaningful relationships and maintain communication with clients and stakeholders, providing continual updates to the simulation progress.

Thermal Analysis & Performance Improvement Engineer
›	Identify root causes, control actions, and implement machine performance improvements earning €3M+ in annual revenue;
›	Execute Design of Experiments to discover the effect of influence factors, run statistical analysis, and generate design improvements and actions based on findings;
›	Work with multidisciplinary stakeholders to set up, execute proper overlay measurements for lens top thermal drifts, and ensure successful outcomes.

RESEARCH THESIS: "Development of an experimental setup for studies of combustion behavior of alternative automotive fuels."

›	Published 3 scientific papers and defended a Ph.D. thesis, "Development of an experimental setup for studies of combustion behaviour of alternative automotive fuels.  
›	Conceptualized a new high-pressure experimental setup to study the combustion of alternative fuels;
›	Responsible for the technical setup and safety during operation;
›	Completed six months of research at the Lund University of Technology in Sweden, applying Laser Induced Fluorescence (LIF) and Laser-Induced Incandescence (LII) techniques;
›	Facilitated a mutually-beneficial partnership with a numerical modelling colleague to run tests and publish a joint publication;  
›	Advised and mentored one undergraduate and four graduate students, in addition to tutoring several undergraduate and master students, championing cooperation and evaluating each student’s progress;
›	Served as the intermediary between TU/e and PETROBRAS, a Brazilian Oil Company to initiate a cooperative research agreement.

Project requested by the Brazilian oil company (PETROBRAS): "Development of a new technology to treat waste water from oil refineries and offshore platforms using natural gas combustion."

›	Liaised with PETROBRAS to develop an innovative technology to treat wastewater from oil refineries and offshore platforms with natural gas combustion;
›	Built a pilot plant for the Brazilian Oil Company PETROBRAS in a joint effort with Ecole Polytechnique Montreal in Canada and private companies in Brazil, fostering a collaborative environment with other researchers, professors, and students;
›	Quickly learn and apply CFD simulations to evaluate performance and recommend design improvements;
›	Defined and designed the final stage of plant building with private engineering companies and the University of Canada.
